28/11/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The new European Commissioner for Enlargement, Olli Rehn, expressed support for Macedonia and confidence in the country's European future, during a visit to Skopje Friday (26 November). Rehn said establishment of a new government and the outcome of the recent decentralisation referendum opened the way for Macedonia to proceed with full implementation of the peace framework agreement -- the main condition for progress towards EU accession, he said. (Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 27/11/04; Makfax - 26/11/04)
